	    <td  bgcolor="dedede"  valign="top" class="msg" width="100%" >
         
          No, don't take out the battery.&nbsp; It doesn't affect battery life.&nbsp; I believe the only thing that affects battery life with a lithium-ion battery is endless drain-and-refill over time.&nbsp; I'm not even convinced that it USES the battery when it's plugged in, but I've not read anything definitive on the subject in a while. <br>  <br> Running the laptop 24/7 is another issue, however.&nbsp; There are other factors at work, including fan operation.&nbsp; If you hear a high speed fan kicking in from time to time after you've been running the laptop for a while, it might not be a good idea.&nbsp; I have mixed feelings in this area.&nbsp; It really is supposed to be able to handle 24/7 operations, but I'm not convinced these modern laptop cases, equipped with faster-spinning hard drives and fancy graphics cards, are able to cool themselves properly over long usage durations. <br>  
          
		  <span class="info">
          					
			</span>
		  <br><br>_____________________________<br><br><a href="http://hardrockstars.org/blogs/pats_blog/" target="_blank"><font color="red"><b>My Blog</b></font></a> <br> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=174188" target="_blank">Chantela</a> <br> <img src="http://www.immersiontechnologies.com/jaws.jpg"> 
         
