          &quot;No, don't take out the battery.&nbsp; It doesn't affect battery life.&nbsp; I believe the only thing that affects battery life with a lithium-ion battery is endless drain-and-refill over time&quot; <br>  <br> By leaving the battery you are endless refilling it. If you read any rechargable label they say its best to charge ONLY when its completely drained. Everytime a rechargeable battery is recharged it loses some of it ability to retain that charge. Some hold up better then others. If its NOT using the battery when pluged in then of course you can leave them in there. 
          
