          Right, that's the &quot;old wisdom&quot;, but I don't know if laptops work that way anymore, or if they do, if it matters to a lithium-ion battery.&nbsp;  <br>  <br> On my laptop there's a separate light for &quot;recharge&quot;.&nbsp; It goes out when the battery is fully recharged.&nbsp; Because it's not staying lit, one can surmise that it's not recharging the battery.&nbsp; It'll pop on once in a blue moon to top it off, because batteries drain natually over time even when not in use, but that's negligible.&nbsp;  <br>  <br> The real test is that when I use my laptop on battery, it seem to last for about the same amount of time that it did when I bought it 2.5 years ago.&nbsp; If there's a difference, I can't detect it.&nbsp; And I use my laptop daily on AC power here at home (but not quite 24/7). <br>  
          
		  <span class="info">
          					
			</span>
