		</td>
        
	    <td  bgcolor="dedede"  valign="top" class="msg" width="100%" >
         
          Yes, take the batteries out when running on line power. <br>  <br> Lithium-ion batteries are ideally stored at 40% charge.&nbsp; Room temperature is ok at partial charge.&nbsp; Cooler is better, particularly if you insist on storing the batteries fully charged.&nbsp; Your refrigerator is good if you put the battery in a plastic bag to avoid condensation.&nbsp; The freezer would be too much of a good thing.&nbsp; Fully charged and hot, as when it's plugged in and the machine is running, cuts the lifetime of the battery significantly.&nbsp;  <br>  <br> (For example, one year of storage/operation at 100% charge and 40 C means the battery will permanently lose about 40% of its capacity.&nbsp; Storage at 40% charge and 25 C will lose about 4%.&nbsp; Much better to drain the battery halfway and leave it in the closet than to leave it in a running laptop.) <br>  <br>  <br>  
          
		  <span class="info">
          					
			</span>
		 
         
         <div align="right">
         <br><span class="ultrasmall">(in reply to <a href='#183661'>nedd</a>)</span>
         
