	    <td  bgcolor="dedede"  valign="top" class="msg" width="100%" >
         
          Interesting, but there's no way that my battery (2+ years old) has lost 64% of its original capacity.&nbsp; But I guess those were 24/7 figures, right?&nbsp; So basically at 1/3 up-time (5-6 days a week for 6-8 hours a day) I'd be looking at something like a 20% hit after two years?&nbsp; Sound about right? <br>  <br> There <i>could </i>be that much loss in there now.&nbsp; I doubt it, but I'd have to really time it to be sure.&nbsp; My guess would be more like 10%.&nbsp; In other words, in spite of heavy, daily, intense usage, I doubt the battery has lost more than 10% of its original capacity.&nbsp; But that's a completely subjective guess. <br>  <br> So I think it's probably a little silly to remove the battery every time you plug it into the wall.&nbsp; I guess I could see it if you're planning to run it (and have it <i>actually processing data</i>, not sitting idle) 24/7, though. <br>  
          
