	    <td  bgcolor="dedede"  valign="top" class="msg" width="100%" >
         
          You're also causing extra heat issues leaving the battery installed.&nbsp; This causes the charging circuits to cycle on an off to monitor the battery and try and top it off. <br>  <br>  <br> Another thing to consider is the life of the backlight for the LCD, while these have improved greatly if you leave the screen going with a saver or just on desktop you'll wear it out sooner and in most cases you can't replace them. <br>  <br> Also on the heat issue, laptops do have heat issues which is why most use a power scaling processor.&nbsp; Leaving them on without the room temp at a constant 70 degrees, will cause degredation of the electronics and motors/bearings in the computer.&nbsp; Since most people don't have their rooms in a controlled environment, you should probably cycle it off to cool down. 
          
		  <span class="info">
          					
			</span>
