	    <td  bgcolor="dedede"  valign="top" class="msg" width="100%" >
         
          Lithium ion batteries are dependent purely on how many times they're refilled - being plugged in should not effect its life span.&nbsp;  <br>   <br>  Lithium ion batteries are generally sold with a pre determined number of &quot;cycles&quot; which is constituted as a fill from empty to full, there are of course partial cycles use if you refill it when its not empty. <br>   <br>  Over time, it does wear down the capacity to carry a charge and eventually after a long time period will stay at 50% for a long time after several hundred charges are used. <br>   <br>  Conventional wisdom says replace it every couple of years. 
          
